	   <tr><td colspan=2>POC to fix faction.<br>I killed Master Whopal in Nek forrest to get a halfling mask (my faction from PKing hummies needed a bit of extra help and the mask moved me from threat to dubious in South Qeynos).  Then I moved to LR and killed bandits for their bandit sashes (LR is a dark team owned zone on the PvP servers, safer).  My first time I turned in 70 sashes in halfling form from the mask in South Qeynos.  Luckily there is a merchant there to sell all the bronze that weighs you down from the quest reward when you turn in the sashes.  The faction hits I took were pleanty to move me from threat to indifferent with the guards, Paladins, and the Temple of Life (ones who give the quest), even in DE form.  My bloodsaber faction (evil hummie guilds in the catacombs of Qeynos)is gone though, but who cares, they did not like me anyway.  I have probably turned in another 160 to 200 sashes and am now warm in faction.  The temple of life loves me as do the good guards.  Couple things of note, there are "raiders" in SK that drop bandit sashes too.  They are along the water line between the bridge to NK and the treant camp.  I think there is 7 of them there.  Also killing the Putrid skeletons at Grimrot's camp will get you faction (but it is very small compared to the sash qeust).  So, while you camp Grim, kill the putrids and then every once in a while run over to the water and wipe out all the bandits.  Soon you will get pleanty of sashes and faction hits all while camping Grim (which is a LONG camp!).  Now if that stupid undead Grim will spawn, then this DE will soon be wearing a nice new shield from lighty land on his back.  BTW, it is fun as heck walking right through the front gates of Qeynos past the guards as a DE on a PvP server as all the lighties freak out!<br><br>Auz<br>Vallon FG<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
