	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello everyone,<br>This is a very ardous quest as I'm sure you have figured out so far.  I wanted to say a few things about my trials during this quest.  As far as killing him at different times of the day to get the different spawn types...&lt;shrug&gt; I did the 5&5 and the 7&7 and it never ensured that what I wanted would pop.  But since everyone that dosnt' agree with this method says just kill it whenever, why not.  As far as all that goes, Do yourself a favor and bind right in front of where he spawns.  Every time you get a chance log in and check to see if he's there.  If you get the PH, you know when you kill him he's gonna be back in 3-3.5 hours.  Just be persistant.  You will get him eventually.  In between spawns a good way to kill time is to hunt the RAIDERS that spawn east of the stone bridge along the water, about halfway to the treants.  They are not bandits but do drop sashes that you can turn in to the pally guy in Qeynos and get faction for this quest.  Second, about having enough faction to complete it.  If you talk to Camlend Serbold and say "Lord Grimrot" this will start his speech about the quest.  If he asks you if you are ready to "defend life"  then you DO have enough faction with him to turn in the components.  This happens when you have WARMLY faction with him.  Hope this helps at least someone out there.  <br><br>Zedeki, Cleric of Marr<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
