	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 5th 11:19 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got aegis of life in 2 real life days..This is how its done but this is gonna be brief for I dont have much time.<br><br>Undead version:<br>Go to skele camp in Sk. Look for a putrid skeleton that is already standing up. Note that all but one putrid skeleton is standing up. The only standing putrid is the Place holder of either version. If you see the standing putrid wait to kill him till 5am ish eq time. Now the next spawn will be either the undead grim or another standing putrid. If its the grim then grats! If its another ph dont kill until 5am ish again. The spawn time for either the ph or grim is 3 hours 15 minutes on average, varies from 3 hours to 3 hours 30 mins. So log out of the game and set a timer if you like thats what I did =)<br><br>Live version:<br>Same thing as above, same spawn times except you gotta kill the ph around 5pm eq time. Now for the live version, you will get lots of phs, if you get a ph wait to kill him around 5pm again-This is important people. I got 4 phs for the live grim rot, And I only got 1 ph for the undead version.<br><br>I got aegis in 2 real life days but I was not on line much. I timed all the spawns and logged off and logged back on a little early before the ph/grim spawn.<br><br>Not sure if you HAVE to kill the phs at 5 am or 5pm but that is what I did. If you do not kill them 5am ish or 5pm ish at least be consistent with your kill times of the phs! Grim is a random spawn but can be helped out by killing his phs at consistent times! There is no despawn people. And there is no 12am 12pm crap!<br><br>Faction:<br>I did soulire and my faction is already pretty good. I did do the fish quest for about an hour near the temple of life. I then turned in my no drop stuff and presto I got it!!!<br><br>Good luck<br>51 cavalier<br>Bristlebane<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
